file_insights.insight: Added imports and exports for ChecklistInstance and ChecklistItemResponse models from checklist_template module
Added .auto-claude/ directory to gitignore to exclude auto-generated Claude configuration files
Auto-generated security configuration file defining allowed base commands, stack commands, and detected project stack (Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, PostgreSQL, Redis, Docker)
Auto-generated status tracking file showing 5/9 subtasks completed, session 5 in progress, model implementation phase
Auto-generated Claude settings with sandbox enabled, granular file permissions, and MCP integrations (linear-server, graphiti-memory)

patterns_discovered.description: Standard Python package pattern of importing models in __init__.py to expose public API
patterns_discovered.example: Importing ChecklistInstance and ChecklistItemResponse then adding to __all__ list

patterns_discovered.description: Automated Claude workflow system managing task orchestration with security, status, and settings files
Breaking down larger specifications into numbered subtasks with individual completion tracking
patterns_discovered.example: Subtask 1-5 of 9 total subtasks in specification 011-2-2

patterns_discovered.description: Multiple configuration layers for different concerns (security, status, settings)
patterns_discovered.example: Separate JSON files for security rules, execution status, and IDE settings

gotchas_discovered.description: .auto-claude* files are committed to git despite being automation artifacts
gotchas_discovered.impact: These generated files may cause merge conflicts or be outdated if regenerated in different branches
gotchas_discovered.recommendation: Consider adding .auto-claude* to .gitignore similar to .auto-claude/ directory

gotchas_discovered.description: .auto-claude-security.json and .claude_settings.json contain absolute paths specific to user environment
gotchas_discovered.impact: These files will not work correctly on different machines or for different users
gotchas_discovered.recommendation: Use relative paths or environment variables instead of absolute paths in generated config

gotchas_discovered.description: Very granular permission rules with full paths to task directories may need frequent updates
gotchas_discovered.impact: New tasks may require manual permission configuration updates
gotchas_discovered.recommendation: Consider using glob patterns or role-based permissions instead

approach_outcome.task_description: Update model __init__.py to export new models
approach_outcome.primary_achievement: Successfully added ChecklistInstance and ChecklistItemResponse to model exports
approach_outcome.secondary_changes: Generated auto-claude infrastructure files and updated .gitignore
approach_outcome.approach_summary: Straightforward export addition following established Python package patterns with automated infrastructure provisioning

recommendations.rationale: These are environment-specific and auto-generated files that should not be version controlled

recommendations.recommendation: Use relative paths or environment variables in generated configuration files instead of absolute paths
recommendations.rationale: Improves portability and reduces merge conflicts across different development machines

recommendations.recommendation: Document model import dependencies in comments or separate diagram
recommendations.rationale: Growing number of models (12 exported) makes it harder to track relationships and circular dependencies

recommendations.recommendation: Create a template or schema for .auto-claude configuration files for consistency
recommendations.rationale: Multiple auto-generated files should follow consistent patterns and structure

recommendations.recommendation: Consider tracking subtask status outside of git-committed files
recommendations.rationale: Status tracking should be ephemeral and user-specific, not part of repository history
